The paper deals with the problem of sub-Nyquist sampling of analog signals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on multiband signals, which are sparse in the frequency domain, making it likely that the paper falls under the subcategory of sparse signal processing (cs.SI). The proposed system involves hardware implementation and digital processing, which could also place it in the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
